content: Created `pyproject.toml` defining minimal project metadata and registering the `run_benchmark` console-script entrypoint (`qg_bench.cli:main`), including package data for `schema.json` and the example JSONL dataset.

output.code:
from pathlib import Path
import json

target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('pyproject.toml')
target_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

chunks = [
"""[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=68", "wheel"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta\""",
"""[project]
name = "qg-bench"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Minimal benchmark CLI that computes observables and writes standardized results."
readme = ""
requires-python = ">=3.9"
license = {text = "MIT"}
authors = [{name = "OpenAI", email = "noreply@example.com"}]
dependencies = []

[project.scripts]
run_benchmark = "qg_bench.cli:main\""",
"""[tool.setuptools]
packages = ["qg_bench"]

[tool.setuptools.package-data]
qg_bench = ["schema.json", "data/*.jsonl"]"""
]

final_text = '\n'.join(block.strip('\n') for block in chunks).strip() + '\n'
target_path.write_text(final_text, encoding='utf-8')

print('FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml')
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
